parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the wiring under the steering column can cause a burning odor, smoke, and melting of plastic components, leading to a potential fire hazard and electrical system failure.
symptoms: intermittent failure of ignition switch to turn over
failure of accessories such as A/C

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed sensor can cause inaccurate speedometer and odometer readings, which can lead to issues with vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: The speedometer and odometer readings are inaccurate
the speed sensor part breaks repeatedly
the bolt attaching the speed sensor to the transmission cracks across its diameter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to roll downhill when parked, even when the transmission is in park, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls downhill when parked uphill
the transmission fails to engage park properly
the vehicle moves unexpectedly when in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel gauge can lead to inaccurate fuel level readings, causing drivers to run out of fuel unexpectedly, which can result in stranded vehicles, accidents, or even engine damage.
symptoms: The fuel gauge needle fluctuates or sticks
the fuel gauge does not move
the vehicle runs out of fuel despite the gauge indicating otherwise.
